      • mergeNodeRoleDimensions

        public static void mergeNodeRoleDimensions(java.nio.file.Path dataPath,
                                           java.util.SortedSet<NodeRoleDimension> newDimensions,
                                           java.lang.String defaultDimension,
                                           boolean deleteAutoFirst)
                                    throws java.io.IOException
        Merge the dimensions in current file with new data. If the same dimension is present in both data sources, the new data wins. If defaultDimension is non-null, it is deemed as the default dimension. Optionally, delete all dimensions of type AUTO before adding new data.
        Parameters:
        dataPath - Location of the old data
        newDimensions - The new role data. Null values are treated as if the map were empty.
        defaultDimension - Dimension to deem as default after merger
        deleteAutoFirst - If dimensions of type AUTO should be deleted first
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException
